WEBVTT

00:15:59.261 --> 00:16:01.198
(Laughter) (Applause)

00:16:01.198 --> 00:16:05.250
So anyway, you may say, this 
puzzle, the mystery of existence,

00:16:05.250 --> 00:16:06.668
it's just silly mystery-mongering.

00:16:06.668 --> 00:16:10.535
You're not astonished at the existence of the universe

00:16:10.535 --> 00:16:12.170
and you're in good company.

00:16:12.170 --> 00:16:14.386
Bertrand Russell said,

00:16:14.386 --> 00:16:18.041
"I should say the universe is just there, and that's all."

00:16:18.041 --> 00:16:19.442
Just a brute fact.

00:16:19.442 --> 00:16:22.276
And my professor at Columbia, Sidney Morgenbesser,

00:16:22.276 --> 00:16:23.985
a great philosophical wag,

00:16:23.985 --> 00:16:25.602
when I said to him, "Professor Morgenbesser,

00:16:25.602 --> 00:16:28.098
why is there something rather than nothing?"

00:16:28.098 --> 00:16:30.248
And he said, "Oh, even if there was nothing,